Thanks frens. You guys are the best! I understand what you mean, and I'm completely open for suggestions and what not whenever you have them. I love this idea! This whole project sounds awesome. Now onto the topic of Caniformia. I think it's a splendid idea, but I have one thing I would like to add. Whatever sentient anthros in this world, be it wolfs, foxes, or raccoons; I think they should be omnivorous, much like humans. This means that no strictly herbivorous or carnivorous species is anthropomorphic. They are simply still animals. My reasoning for this belief is quite possibly foolish, but I feel as though no species that wasn't omnivorous would've had the opportunity to evolve and gain sentience and sapience. Their diets, carnivores and herbivores, are lacking in biodiversity, and do not lend well to brain growth. Although if you can convince me other wise I may reconsider. I'm not exactly an expert, much less coherent, when it comes to this stuff. I guess I could leave that up to you, fren. Moving along, my reasons for choosing wolf's as the main anthro would be due to their natural omnivorous diet. This ties together with my earlier reasoning. As a geologist (according to my undergrad degree) I have a much more evolutionary perspective on how species are related. I was never really up on the modern day families & relations, much more of following family trees from root to canopy, beginning from fundamental kingdoms.


>>38096199
Glad to hear you're excited about it. First suggestion along these lines is not to make too many hard decisions early. There is time. For some thoughts, make sure to take a day or two or even longer to let your imagination build the structure in your head, including the unconscious biases you want to include and exclude.

Regarding diet, probably keep it simple. It's a fantasy world, so go with "mostly like humans in our world, maybe ~80% match." That way there's room for junkfood jokes and taking a piss on fast food, while different species will gravitate slightly toward certain preferences. And they have some good bantz at each other over "How can you eat THAT?" with occasional "Holy crap! This is AMAZING!"

So your awoos probably like more meat, and they like it pretty bleeding rare in many cases. Other individuals & cultures enjoy a bit more preparation & refinement using more herbs & seasonings. There'll always be the wolf that is into cheese and wine-basted, well-roasted chicken, and the tanuki chef that specializes in and has a personal taste for sashimi, as well as fine selections of very rare beef and venison.

Everybody likes cake. That's just a universal given.

Quick tech note from last thread: I suggest 2nd gen smart phones, so circa 2010-2012, and possibly more 1990s retro tech for some "other things." I want to believe this is a pretty green society, very nature oriented & pollution-adverse. So similar & familiar to Earth, but slightly alternate timeline/universe. Which allows for humans to crossover, somehow, from our Earth. I have thoughts on this I can't drill into right now, but it would explain the human myth & prep the way for them to visit.

Okay, so what type of sub-nationality we talking here?
There are the Sami, Bornholmsk, Scanians, and (if you ask the right people) Gotlander, and Jutland cultures as the ones I can list off top of my head.

There is the Sami, a non-Scandinavian culture similar to the Finns along the northern Norwegian-Swedish border, there are the Åland peoples which are a mix of Finnish-Swedish, and Baltic culture.
So are you looking for a Non-Scandinavian or Non-Nordic subgroup? Because the Nordic peoples are the Scandinavians and the Northern Finnic peoples, which some also include the Estonians (I personally do but that's because I dislike Swedes)
There used to be some other Scandinavian cultures in the British Isles, France, Italy, the Baltics Germany, Lebanon (some debate whether or not the Lebanese are a mix of Norman-Arab culture rather than pure Arab)

Give me the details about the situation, there are some things to consider
